15:30.973 --> 15:33.802
Oh, for God's sakes,
take the stairs.

15:34.934 --> 15:36.718
♪ ♪

15:41.679 --> 15:45.857
Where the hell is my
big-eyed character witness?

15:45.945 --> 15:48.860
My guess? Unspooling
a fireman's hose.

15:50.384 --> 15:51.472
What?

15:51.559 --> 15:53.953
She's banging
a fireman.

15:54.040 --> 15:57.043
I am going away
for a long time.

15:57.130 --> 15:58.261
You know...

15:58.348 --> 16:01.221
it's not too
late to run.

16:01.308 --> 16:02.787
You think?

16:02.874 --> 16:04.267
[door opens]

16:04.354 --> 16:05.616
Regina, I can't
delay this anymore.

16:05.703 --> 16:08.706
Now it's too
late to run.

16:08.793 --> 16:10.273
Oh, dear God,

16:10.360 --> 16:12.319
I prayed it wouldn't
come to this.

16:12.406 --> 16:12.710
But...

16:14.538 --> 16:16.323
Sketchy...

16:16.410 --> 16:17.672
will you be
my character witness?

16:20.762 --> 16:23.547
I would be honored.

16:23.634 --> 16:25.549
The judge a guy
or a girl?

16:25.636 --> 16:26.594
Guy.

16:27.638 --> 16:30.032
I got this.

16:34.210 --> 16:36.647
Your Honor, I'm not
gonna candy-coat it.

16:36.734 --> 16:39.563
I've done bad things in my life.

16:44.699 --> 16:47.615
I've bought drugs, sold drugs,
a little gun smuggling,

16:47.702 --> 16:50.618
might have dabbled
in some human trafficking.

16:50.705 --> 16:54.796
But that doesn't mean
I'm not a good person today.

16:54.883 --> 16:59.322
[quietly]: Doesn't mean she's a
good character witness, either.

16:59.409 --> 17:01.107
I've sat where Regina
Thompkins is sitting.

17:01.194 --> 17:03.413
I know the regret
she's feeling,

17:03.500 --> 17:05.502
the shame, because
she hurt innocent people.

17:05.589 --> 17:07.983
Yes, you did, Regina.

17:08.069 --> 17:11.377
You hurt them.
Don't look away.

17:13.423 --> 17:15.991
But what are we here for,
Your Honor...

17:16.078 --> 17:18.733
punishment or redemption?

17:20.778 --> 17:23.215
Okay, I'll
say it for you.

17:23.303 --> 17:25.044
Redemption.

17:25.131 --> 17:29.004
Which is why Irecommend
release with probation,

17:29.091 --> 17:31.485
so Regina can find
honest employment

17:31.572 --> 17:34.053
and pay back
the money she stole.

17:34.140 --> 17:36.620
You do realize we're
talking about $3 million.

17:36.707 --> 17:40.363
Well, they may
not get it tomorrow...

17:40.450 --> 17:41.582
but doesn't she
deserve a chance?

17:41.669 --> 17:44.193
I don't think so.

17:44.280 --> 17:45.847
Wow.

17:45.934 --> 17:47.675
So you're just gonna be
a douche about this.

17:47.762 --> 17:50.286
I'm here, I'm here. Sorry.

17:50.373 --> 17:52.593
Oh, thank God!
Get your skinny
ass up there!

17:53.768 --> 17:54.725
Tough crowd.

17:54.812 --> 17:57.859
Hi. Sorry I'm late.

17:57.946 --> 17:59.861
Today has been
a total nightmare.

17:59.948 --> 18:01.906
Do I need to, uh,
touch a Bible

18:01.993 --> 18:04.126
or say the Pledge
of Allegiance or something?

18:04.213 --> 18:05.780
No, no, just
state your name

18:05.867 --> 18:07.738
and tell us about
the defendant.

18:07.825 --> 18:09.958
Oh, okay. Uh...

18:10.045 --> 18:12.003
Christy Plunkett.

18:12.091 --> 18:16.660
I'm... here to speak
on behalf of Regina Thompkins.

18:16.747 --> 18:18.619
Whew! Where to start?

18:18.706 --> 18:21.839
I mean... I love her.

18:21.926 --> 18:24.451
She's a wonderful
person.

18:24.538 --> 18:26.757
Sure, she's made some mistakes,

18:26.844 --> 18:29.456
but she's really turned
her life around.

18:29.543 --> 18:31.893
She's been sober
for six months, and...

18:31.980 --> 18:34.025
let me tell you, that
is not an easy thing to do.

18:34.113 --> 18:36.027
Because...

18:36.115 --> 18:37.986
when you get sober, you...

18:38.073 --> 18:41.207
think the fun's over.

18:41.294 --> 18:42.686
Unless you get lucky
and meet a guy

18:42.773 --> 18:45.298
who actually
makes you feel good,

18:45.385 --> 18:47.778
and then you think,
"All right, I'm back!"

18:47.865 --> 18:49.693
But you're not.

18:51.782 --> 18:54.829
[sniffles]

18:54.916 --> 18:56.874
[crying]:
Because...

18:56.961 --> 18:59.573
you open your heart up...

18:59.660 --> 19:01.618
to this jerk...
[sniffles]

19:01.705 --> 19:06.101
and he turns out to be a big,

19:06.188 --> 19:09.757
drunken, cheating idiot.

19:09.844 --> 19:12.238
Yeah, the sex was
great, Your Honor.

19:12.325 --> 19:13.761
But how am I supposed

19:13.848 --> 19:15.502
to forgive him?

19:15.589 --> 19:17.982
Once a liar,
always a liar!

19:18.069 --> 19:20.246
A leopard cannot
change its spots.

19:22.726 --> 19:24.728
Unless, of course,

19:24.815 --> 19:27.818
the leopard is
Regina Thompkins.

19:36.827 --> 19:40.309
Is it too late to give back
some of that money?

19:43.791 --> 19:47.098
I'm so sorry
about the way I acted.

19:47.186 --> 19:48.361
I just thought...

19:48.448 --> 19:50.754
David and I
really had something.

19:50.841 --> 19:52.234
I know, baby.

19:52.321 --> 19:55.542
I'm so sorry you had
to go through that.

19:56.630 --> 19:58.284
Hello?

19:58.371 --> 19:59.894
Anybody sorry I'm going
to jail for four years?

19:59.981 --> 20:01.939
Aw, with good behavior,
you'll be out in two.

20:02.026 --> 20:03.941
You could do two years
standing on your head.

20:04.028 --> 20:06.074
Or sitting on someone else's.

20:06.161 --> 20:08.685
Here's what you do--
first day in there,

20:08.772 --> 20:10.121
you find the biggest badass
in the yard,

20:10.209 --> 20:12.602
hit her with
a sock full of nickels

20:12.689 --> 20:15.388
and show everybody there's
a new queen bitch in town.

20:15.475 --> 20:17.172
But doesn't that mean
sooner or later

20:17.259 --> 20:19.348
someone's gonna whack
the crap out of me?

20:19.435 --> 20:22.264
Well, uneasy lies the head
that wears the crown.

20:23.526 --> 20:24.875
[big sigh]

20:24.962 --> 20:25.746
Anybody else feel
like hitting a meeting?

20:25.833 --> 20:27.878
Sounds good to me.

20:31.055 --> 20:33.101
Don't worry, Regina, your box
of money is safe with me.

